<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ningxia Develops Animal Husbandry Production Bases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ningxia Develops Animal Husbandry Production Bases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0404094794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0649 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0404094794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yinchuan, April 4 (XINHUA) -- The Ningxia Hui 
Autonomous Region, a major animal husbandry base in China, has 
concentrated its strength on building ten animal husbandry 
production bases. 
  The bases cover 144 townships and 214 villages. They produce 
respectively 33.2 percent, 30 percent and 80 percent of the 
total meat, eggs and milk of the region. 
  The per capita milk share in the region is three times the 
average level of the country. 
  Ningxia, a Moslem province and one of the five autonomous 
regions inhabited mainly by minority nationalities, also 
attaches importance to relying on science and technology to 
improve its production. 
  The region has put into application over 30 research 
findings 
and items of technology, and developed new breeds of chickens 
and animals. 
  Its chicken-raising industry has a production value of 175 
million yuan (about 21 million U.S. dollars), and milk 
production is ranked among the top in the country. 
  At the same time, the region has invested over 30 million 
yuan (about 3.6 million U.S. dollars) in 37 infrastructure 
projects in the animal husbandry production bases. 
  According to statistics, more than 153,000 ha of grassland 
have been improved. 
  Last year, the region's total output value of animal 
husbandry was 750 million yuan, 4.65 percent up over the 
previous year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

