<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Attends Ceremony Honoring Emperor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Attends Ceremony Honoring Emperor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0504145694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1432 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0504145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Xian, April 5 (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of 
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference, attended a ceremony in honor of Huangdi 
(Yellow Emperor) here today. 
  Huangdi is a legendary ancestor of the Chinese nation. 
  Chinese officials, topped by Li Ruihuan, who is on an 
inspection tour in Shaanxi, and representatives of Taiwan, Hong 
Kong and Macao compatriots and overseas Chinese presented flower 
baskets to and saluted the Huangdi mausoleum. 
  After the rites concluded, Li Ruihuan planted a 
commemorative 
pine beside the mausoleum. 
  Yesterday, a donation ceremony was also held here for the 
repair and renovation of the mausoleum. Li Ruihuan, honorary 
chairman of the China Huangdi Mausoleum Foundation, made a 
donation of 2,000 yuan. 
  The fund donation started in 1992. The foundation had 
received 6.34 million yuan by the end of last year. 
  More than 13 million yuan were donated to the foundation 
after the donation ceremony ended yesterday. 

</TEXT>

