<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Inscribes for Ancient Dam Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng Inscribes for Ancient Dam Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0504142394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1344 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0504142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Chengdu, April 5 (XINHUA) -- A celebration was 
held today near the capital of Southwest China's Sichuan 
Province for the 2250th anniversary of the Dujiangyan Dam, the 
world's oldest functioning irrigation works. 
  Chinese Premier Li Peng wrote an inscription for the 
occasion 
to praise the project for its great contribution to agriculture 
in Sichuan basin. 
  Residents at Dujiangyan, an hour's bus ride from the 
provincial capital of Chengdu, dressed streets with colorful 
flags, raised lanterns, and posted poetic couplets on their 
doors. [passage omitted] 
  Huge sums of money have been poured into the expansion and 
reconstruction of the project since 1949. Its irrigated areas 
have been increased from 187,000 hectares to about 670,000 
hectares over the past four decades. 
  The dam has become a multi-purpose project combining 
irrigation, flood prevention, power generation, fish breeding 
and sightseeing. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
