<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhu Rongji Reportedly Warns Against Inflation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhu Rongji Reportedly Warns Against Inflation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0604033694 Hong Kong LIEN HO PAO in Chinese 6 Apr 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> HK0604033694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong LIEN HO PAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Report from Hong Kong" by reporter Huang Tien (7806 3944): </F>
"Zhu Rongji Warns Against Inflation, Saying Worsening Inflation 
Will Affect Social Stability"] 
  [Text] Zhu Rongji, vice premier of the State Council on 
the mainland, recently warned against inflation on the mainland. 
He said that the macro environment is so tight, and reform is 
developing in such depth and width, that if the inflationary 
pressure at this moment continues to increase or if serious 
inflation takes place, then social stability will be affected. 
  At a recent meeting of experts, Zhu Rongji warned against 
the 
bad situation that price increases in some mainland cities 
exceeded 40 percent and that grain prices were skyrocketing. 
Zhu Rongji said: Without stability, there is no point in 
talking about anything, and a small incident can disrupt the 
historical process, so we must not pursue speed only, our work 
must be solid. 
  At the meeting, Zhu Rongji said citing Deng Xiaoping's words 
that an overheated economy can easily lead to mistakes, 
development speed must be moderate. When it is too fast and 
completely out of the question, we can do nothing but increase 
the price of goods, but the masses already have fears about 
prices and inflation, and in an economic environment which does 
not allow much room for maneuver, we must correctly handle the 
relations among reform, development, and stability, and the 
overall situation. 
  Summing up the problems arising from the economic 
development 
of last year, Zhu Rongji stressed that the socialist market 
economy needs macroeconomic regulation and control, which is 
very important to the reform of the socialist market economy 
system which will be launched thoroughly this year, but the 
problem is, for a long time we viewed socialism as planned 
economy and capitalism as anarchy. 
  In light of this, Zhu Rongji once again cited Deng 
Xiaoping's 
unpublished words that a market economy is not a sign 
distinguishing a country's social system. Last year, some 
problems emerged from the national economy and financial 
discipline was chaotic while the investment scale was too large, 
which requires us to keep exploring in future practice so as to 
clear a real road. 
  Zhu Rongji also criticized some people's idea that a market 
economy is the special feature of capitalist economy which is 
difficult to link to socialism. He said: Up to now, many 
economists in the world unanimously think that the market 
economy on the mainland has been run very well. At the end of 
the meeting, Zhu Rongji said: From the stance of a socialist 
country, we think our own road is right. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

