<H3> <TI>   U.S. Bank Helps Finance Airlines Purchase of 7 Boeings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Bank Helps Finance Airlines Purchase of 7 Boeings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604222894 Beijing XINHUA in English 2111 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0604222894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New York, April 6 (XINHUA) -- The First National 
Bank of Chicago and Bank of China today jointly announced the 
closing of a 261 million U.S. dollar transaction, backed by an 
Export-Import Bank of the United States (Eximbank) guarantee, to 
finance the purchase by China Southern Airlines (Group) of seven 
Boeing 737 aircraft. 
  Under the deal, which marks the first time that a Chinese 
company will raise long-term funds in the U.S. securities market 
with credit support from Eximbank, the guarantee extends up to 
201 million U.S. dollars, according to the First Bank of Chicago. 
  The remaining 60 million dollars will be financed through a 
syndicated loan arranged by First Chicago Bank and Bank of China 
and guaranteed by the Bank of China. 
  First Chicago Capital Markets, Inc., a subsidiary of First 
Chicago Corporation, is the sole underwriter of the AAA\AAA 
rated certificates, which will be sold to institutional 
investors. 
  The First National Bank of Chicago is the main bank 
subsidiary of First Chicago Corporation, which has 53 billion 
dollars in assets and is the nation's 11th largest bank holding 
company. 

</TEXT>

