<F P=103> OW0704105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 7 (XINHUA) -- Mobil, a leading world 
oil company, is marking the 100th anniversary of its business in 
China by setting up a fund of 500,000 U.S. dollars to help with 
China's education. 
  The corporation presented a 100,000 U.S. dollars check to 
the 
National Academy of Education Administration as the first 
instalment for the fund in support of the academy's efforts to 
upgrade the training facilities and programs for training 
education administrators. 
  With its headquarters in the United States, Mobil started 
its 
Shanghai office 100 years ago and returned to China in 1974. 
Now it has three offices -- in Beijing, Shanghai, and Guangzhou. 
  K. Yuan, chairman and managing director of the Mobil 
Corporation in Hong Kong, said that Mobil has been in China for 
a long time and intends to stay for a lot longer. 

