<H3> <TI>   Qian Qichen Confers With Mongolian Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qian Qichen Confers With Mongolian Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604140494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1309 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0604140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 6 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier 
and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen held talks with visiting 
Mongolian Minister of External Relations Tserenpiliyn Gombosuren 
here this afternoon. 
  The two sides exchanged ideas on enhancing bilateral 
relations and on international issues of common concern. 
  Qian said that there has been satisfactory progress in all 
fields of Sino-Mongolian ties since the normalization of the two 
countries' relations in 1989. 
  He noted that Mongolia is an important neighbor of China, 
with which China is willing to develop good-neighborly ties. 
  Gombosuren said that Mongolia is quite satisfied with the 
growth of the two countries' relations in recent years, adding 
that it is a major part of Mongolia's foreign policy to develop 
friendly relations with China. 
  The two foreign ministers also discussed issues concerning 
Chinese Premier Li Peng's forthcoming Mongolia visit, which they 
both agreed would be of significance in the development of 
bilateral links. 
  After the talks Qian and Gombosuren signed an agreement on 
cooperation between the two foreign ministries. Officials from 
the two countries initialed an agreement on preservation and 
utilization of water along Sino-Mongolian border. 
  Qian also hosted a dinner in honor of Gombosuren and his 
party, who arrived here earlier today. 

</TEXT>

