<H3> <TI>   Discuss Human Rights </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discuss Human Rights </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604173294 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1600 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finnish Premier Esko Aho and Chinese Premier Li Peng 
both say that political and economic relations between Finland 
and China have developed in a favorable way. Aho started an 
official visit to China today. The premiers concentrated on 
economic matters at their meeting. Aho hoped that China's 
willingness to curb the overheating of its economy would not 
have negative consequences for Finland's traditional cooperation 
projects. 
  China's human rights policy was also discussed. Aho 
reiterated Finland's stance that human rights are universal and 
everybody must respect them. According to Premier Li, China 
wants to adhere to the principles accepted at the UN human 
rights conference last year. China is of the opinion that these 
principles give China the right to apply its own cultural 
traditions in this matter. 

</TEXT>

