<H3> <TI>   Beijing, Berlin Officials Discuss Trade Deals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing, Berlin Officials Discuss Trade Deals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604142094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1309 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0604142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 6 (XINHUA) -- An economic and trade 
discussion between Beijing and Berlin, Germany, was held here 
today. 
  Beijing Vice-Mayor Lu Yucheng and Berlin Mayor Eberhard 
Diepgen briefly introduced the two cities' investment 
environments and related economic information. 
  Representatives from more than 70 local enterprises and over 
30 German enterprises discussed more than 200 projects, covering 
automobiles, electronics, light industry, construction 
materials, food, machinery, communications, environmental 
protection and energy. 
  Over the past few years, exchanges and cooperation between 
Beijing and Germany have been on the rise. To date, Beijing has 
an import and export volume of 170 million U.S. dollars with 
Germany. 
  Beijing imports electronic parts, light industrial 
machinery, 
polyester and internal-combustion engine parts from Germany and 
exports clothing and textile products. 
  German businessmen have established nearly 60 enterprises in 
Beijing, involving investments of more than 400 million U.S. 
dollars. Beijing has opened four enterprises in Germany. 
  At the discussion today, German businessmen were satisfied 
with the investment environment in Beijing and showed great 
interest in some projects, sources said. 
  Yesterday, Beijing and Berlin signed a memorandum for 
becoming sister cities. 
  Under a related agreement, the first economic delegation, 
including siemens and benz, and headed by Berlin Mayor Diepgen, 
has started an inspection tour in Beijing. It will also go to 
Shanghai and Shenzhen. 

</TEXT>

