<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Urges Protection of Huangdi Mausoleum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Urges Protection of Huangdi Mausoleum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604142394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1358 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0604142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Xian, April 6 (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of 
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference, recently urged local officials here to 
better protect the Huangdi Mausoleum. 
  Li Ruihuan is a member of the Standing Committee of the 
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party 
of China and honorary chairman of the China Huangdi Foundation. 
  Huangdi (Yellow Emperor) is a legendary ancestor of the 
Chinese nation and yesterday was a traditional festival on which 
Chinese commemorate their ancestors. 
  The Huangdi Mausoleum was of great significance for 
fostering 
Chinese culture, stimulating patriotism, strengthening national 
integration and advancing the modernization drive, Li said. 
  In the course of the Chinese modernization drive, how to 
unite overseas compatriots to the maximum extent and give full 
play to their potential and intelligence has always been a major 
topic, Li said. He pointed out that Huangdi is a highly 
representative figure in the history of the Chinese nation. 
  He called on the local government to give strong support to 
the repair and renovation of the mausoleum and to collect funds 
through public donations. 
  He noted that there must be a long-term plan for the repair 
and protection of the mausoleum. 
  Li Ruihuan conducted an investigation in Shaanxi Province on 
April 3-6. He inspected the No. 2 pit of the terracotta 
warriors being excavated and attended the public rites in honor 
of Huangdi yesterday. 

</TEXT>

