<H3> <TI>   Spokesman: Wei's Secretary `Being Investigated' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman: Wei's Secretary `Being Investigated' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0704072894 Hong Kong AFP in English 0657 GMT 7 April 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK0704072894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 7 (AFP)--The secretary of Wei 
Jingsheng, China's leading dissident, is undergoing police 
investigation, a Ministry of Public Security spokesman said 
Thursday. Tong Yi, who disappeared on Monday, "is currently 
being investigated," the spokesman said, using a term indicating 
that she was also in police detention. 
  Tong has acted as chief spokesperson for Wei since he was 
released from prison in September, acting as go-between for the 
dissident and foreign journalists. Tong was travelling in a car 
with Wei when he was picked up Friday as he attempted to return 
to Beijing. 
  The spokesman refused to specify what crimes Tong was being 
investigated for. 

