<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian Encourages Coast-Mountain Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujian Encourages Coast-Mountain Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704022794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0211 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704022794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fuzhou, April 7 (XINHUA) -- East China's Fujian 
Province is encouraging economic co-operation between the 
coastal and mountainous areas where developments are uneven. 
  The coastal cities of Fuzhou, Xiamen and Quanzhou concluded 
hundreds of agreements on economic co-operation with the 
mountainous prefectures of Ningde, Longyan, Sanming and Nanping 
last year, with the former providing capital, technology and 
information to the latter. 
  The Sanming city alone signed 154 contract on economic 
co-operation with the coastal cities of Putian, Quanzhou and 
Xiamen, involving a total investment of 400 million yuan. The 
contracts cover the building materials, forestry and chemical 
industries, according to Guan Qing, chairman of the provincial 
economic cooperation office. 
  The economy in the coastal areas of the province is growing 
faster than the mountainous thanks to the policy of opening to 
the outside world. The provincial move is believed to be part 
of the nation-wide bid to narrow the gap between those 
comparatively developed and underdeveloped areas. 

</TEXT>

