BFN 

  [Excerpt] The digital communications network which 
provides various modernized communications means has recently 
been completed and made available in the province. This is an 
indication that the comprehensive communications capacity of the 
province's postal and telecommunications departments has joined 
the world's high ranks. 
  The digital communications network is a new communications 
method combining computers with modern communications 
technology. The digital communications network now available in 
the province is a network with diverse functions and group 
exchanges and is of a high world level. With this equipment, 
the province is able to conduct digital communications with all 
cities at or above the city and prefectural levels in the 
province, with 30 capital cities, most cities at or above the 
city and prefectural levels, and some cities at the county level 
in the country, and with 23 countries and regions in the world, 
including the United States, Japan, France, and Germany. 
