<H3> <TI>   Li Lanqing on Import Role of Auto Trading Center </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Lanqing on Import Role of Auto Trading Center </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704104394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1021 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 7 (XINHUA) -- The China Automobile 
Import and Trading Center should be the main channel for 
importing automobiles, said Vice-Premier Li Lanqing. 
  He told a working conference of the center that the center 
should do well in services and not seek profits. 
  The premier said that there should be other channels for 
importing automobiles but they should be subject to 
macro-economic control. 
  He encouraged automobile importing firms to import more 
technology in order to upgrade China's auto industry which is on 
the road to maturity. 
  The China Auto Import and Trading Center, a legal entity, 
was 
approved by the State Council in June last year. Since then, it 
has imported 14,000 automobiles from the United States and 
formulated relevant marketing rules. It has also carried out 
bonded businesses for imports and barter trade. 

</TEXT>

