<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turpan-Hami Oilfield Increases Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turpan-Hami Oilfield Increases Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704065394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0623 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704065394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Urumqi, April 7 (XINHUA) -- The Turpan-Hami oilfield 
in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region will be 
able to pump 24.5 million bbl (over three million tons) of crude 
oil annually by the end of 1995, according to an oilfield 
official. 
  Located in the 48,000 sq km Turpan-Hami basin, the oilfield 
is currently capable of producing 1.58 million tons a year, the 
official said, adding that it pumped 1.15 million tons in 1993. 
  The recoverable oil reserves of the oilfield are estimated 
at 
1.6 billion tons, and its natural gas reserves at 365 billion cu 
m [cubic meters]. 
  Drilling of the oilfield began three years ago. So far six 
oil- gas-fields and nine oil- and gas-bearing structures have 
been discovered. 

</TEXT>

