<H3> <TI>   French Prime Minister Balladur Arrives in Beijing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    French Prime Minister Balladur Arrives in Beijing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704014594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0125 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704014594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 7 (XINHUA) -- French Prime Minister 
Edouard Balladur flew in here today to begin his four-day 
official visit to China. 
  The visit, the first by a French head of government in the 
past 16 years, is seen here as an important political move which 
will produce fresh impetus to the Sino-French relations. 
  Accompanying the prime minister on the visit were French 
Foreign Minister Alain Juppe, Industry, Posts and Foreign Trade 
Minister Gerard Longuet and other senior officials and 
parliamentarians. 
  Greeting the prime minister and the delegation he is leading 
at the airport were Shi Dazhen, chairman of the Chinese 
Government Reception Committee and minister of power industry, 
and other senior Chinese officials. 
  Balladur is scheduled to have formal talks with Chinese 
Premier Li Peng this afternoon. 

</TEXT>

