<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian To Tighten Regulations on Overseas Investors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujian To Tighten Regulations on Overseas Investors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704073794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0629 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704073794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fuzhou, April 7 (XINHUA) -- The Fujian provincial 
authorities have issued a set of provisional regulations to 
tighten the management of investment by overseas companies in 
the form of assets. 
  A leading official of the provincial commodity inspection 
bureau said that the regulations are intended to protect the 
legitimate rights and interests of both Chinese and overseas 
investors, and meet the needs of opening Fujian wider to the 
outside world and deepening the reforms. 
  He said that, in accordance with the regulations, his bureau 
and its subsidiaries are in charge of evaluating assets of 
foreign investment, primarily machinery and equipment. 
  Meanwhile, the provincial departments of foreign trade and 
economic cooperation, planning, finance, industry and commerce, 
and taxation will assist the provincial commodity inspectors in 
evaluating such assets, he added. 
  In accordance with the regulations, a contract on the 
establishment of an overseas-funded enterprise must contain an 
article stating that imported assets of foreign investment are 
subject to evaluation by the provincial commodity inspection 
bureau and other government departments. 
  The authorities will not approve the establishment of any 
overseas-funded enterprise if its contract does not contain such 
an article, the official said. 
  He explained that in recent years more overseas companies 
have put machinery and equipment as investment in co-production 
projects with Chinese firms. 
  Machinery and equipment currently account for at least 90 
percent of investment by overseas partners in overseas-funded 
companies in Fujian, he said. 
  He criticized some overseas business people for resorting to 
fraud in this regard. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-2215 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi067_p_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-067 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  6 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

