<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Defends 12-Year Term for Hong Kong Journalist </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Defends 12-Year Term for Hong Kong Journalist </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0704125694 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in Chinese 1145 GMT 
7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0704125694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 7 Apr (ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE)--Foreign 
Ministry Spokesman Wu Jianmin said this afternoon that reporters 
acquiring essential information to promote the development of 
economic relations and trade is different from stealing state 
commercial, financial, and economic secrets, and we should not 
confuse the two. 
  A few days ago, Xi Yang, a reporter with Hong Kong's MING 
PAO, was pronounced guilty by China's judicial organ on the 
charge of "stealing state secrets" and will serve a 12-year 
prison sentence. 
  At a regular news briefing held here on Thursday afternoon, 
Wu Jianmin answered Hong Kong reporters' questions on Xi Yang's 
sentence. He said that as China is opening up more deeply to 
the outside world, it is entirely justified for the overseas 
community to acquire more information about us. The Chinese 
side also publishes, in a timely fashion, statistical 
information through various means, such as granting interviews 
to reporters, and makes public all sorts of information related 
to China through other channels, and our purpose is to promote 
the development of economic relations and trade between China 
and the outside world. 
  Wu Jianmin said that every country had its own commercial 
and 
economic secrets. In cases where someone has stolen such 
secrets, he should definitely be punished. 
  Finally, Wu Jianmin said: If necessary, the Foreign Ministry 
Information Department will, as in the past, organize news 
briefings and invite relevant government officials responsible 
for economic affairs to brief overseas reporters on certain 
aspects of economic construction and development they want to 
know about. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

