<H3> <TI>   Japan-U.S. Trade Talks To `Remain Deadlocked' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan-U.S. Trade Talks To `Remain Deadlocked' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0804094994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0925 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0804094994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Japan-U.S. Trade Talks Deadlocked" -- XINHUA headline] </F>
  [Text] Tokyo, April 8 (XINHUA) -- Japan-U.S. trade talks 
will remain deadlocked due to Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa's 
resignation, TV reports said today. 
  The reports quoted a Ministry of International Trade and 
Industry official as saying that "the development will be 
unclear" despite the fact that talks between Japanese Foreign 
Minister Tsutomu Hata and U.S. Trade Representative Mickey 
Kantor are likely to be resumed next week. 
  Hata is expected to meet Kantor in Marrakech, Morroco next 
week at the signing ceremony for the global trade pact concluded 
in the Uruguay Round last December under the General Agreement 
on Tariffs and Trade. 

</TEXT>

