<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NPC Vice-Chairman Meets Kazakhstan Procurator-General </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0804104294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0956 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0804104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 8 (XINHUA) -- Lei Jieqiong, 
vice-chairman of China's National People's Congress (NPC) 
Standing Committee, met with a delegation from Kazakhstan led by 
Procurator-General Tuyakbaev here this afternoon. 
  Lei said China and Kazakhstan have enjoyed very good 
relations and contacts between high-level officials increased 
since the two countries established diplomatic ties in 1992. 
  Strengthening mutual understanding and friendship between 
the 
judicial departments will be beneficial to the growth of 
bilateral ties, she said. 
  Tuyakbaev said the Kazakhstan Government and people are 
looking forward to Chinese Premier Li Peng's forthcoming visit 
to their country, believing that this visit will give an impetus 
to the existing good bilateral ties and trade. 
  During the meeting Lei briefed the visitors on the NPC's 
composition and functions. 

