<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Interviews Mongolian Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Interviews Mongolian Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704142994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1310 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 7 (XINHUA) -- The development of 
relations between Mongolia and China enjoys a promising 
prospect, said visiting Mongolian Minister of External Relations 
Tserenpiliyn Gombosuren. 
  In an exclusive interview with XINHUA here this afternoon, 
Gombosuren voiced his satisfaction over the talks with Chinese 
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen yesterday and meeting with Premier 
Li Peng this afternoon. 
  He said there would be "two important events" in 
Sino-Mongolian ties this year. One is Chinese Premier Li peng's 
Mongolia visit at the end of this month, and the other the 
upcoming China visit by Chairman Nachagyn Bagabandy of the 
Mongolian State Great Hural. 
  The high-level exchange of visits between the two countries 
would be of major significance in the development of bilateral 
links, he added. 
  Gombosuren noted that the two countries' economic and trade 
relations have been expanding in recent years. Last year 
Mongolia's trade volume with China, in which border trade played 
an important role, accounted for one-fourth of the country's 
total trade volume. 
  He pointed out that there exist great potential and a bright 
future in the cooperation between the two countries in such 
fields as fuel, power and transportation. 
  He stressed that it is the priority of Mongolia's foreign 
policy to develop friendly relations with China and Russia, two 
neighbors of Mongolia. 
  Gombosuren and his party arrived here yesterday. In addition 
to Beijing they are also scheduled to tour Tianjin and Nanjing. 

</TEXT>

