<H3> <TI>   Ambassador to Egypt Meets `Arafat 8 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ambassador to Egypt Meets `Arafat 8 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0804105094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1025 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0804105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, April 8 (XINHUA) -- Palestinian President 
Yasir 'Arafat met with Chinese Ambassador to Egypt Yang Fuchang 
Thursday [7 April]. 
  'Arafat reviewed the latest developments of the Middle East 
peace process, particularly the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations 
on implementing the September 13 accord on Palestinian self-rule 
in the Gaza Strip and the West Bank area of Jericho. 
  'Arafat hoped that the negotiations will make headway as 
soon 
as possible and the accord on Palestinian self-rule will be put 
into effect in time. 
  The Chinese ambassador told 'Arafat that China supports the 
persistent efforts made by the Palestine Liberation Organization 
and the parties concerned to push forward the Middle East peace 
negotiations. 
  Yang said he hoped that a just and comprehensive peace will 
be brought about in the Middle East as early as possible through 
negotiations. 
  'Arafat arrived here Wednesday for consultations with 
President Husni Mubarak of Egypt on all peace-related issues, 
especially the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations. 

</TEXT>

