<H3> <TI>   Beijing Launches `Youth Civilization' Campaign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing Launches `Youth Civilization' Campaign </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0804090394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0839 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0804090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 8 (XINHUA) -- Four exemplary youth 
groups from China's Civil Aviation Departments were named "youth 
civilization models" here today. 
  They are the first set of "youth civilization models" set up 
in the country, said an official from the Central Committee of 
the Chinese Communist Youth League (CCYL). 
  These models are expected to cause other youth groups to 
improve their services and produce more youth civilization 
models across the country, said the official. 
  The campaign, launched by the CCYL Central Committee, is 
aimed to promote professional ethics among Chinese youth and 
help them improve their devotion to work and serving the people. 
  The official said each enterprise from all trades in the 
country has been called on to set up its youth civilization 
models in the next year or two. 

</TEXT>

