<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Report on Leaders' Activities 1-7 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Report on Leaders' Activities 1-7 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0804084294 </F>
<F P=103> OW0804084294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] PRC media monitored by Okinawa Bureau 
carried the following reports on PRC leadership activities from 
1 through 7 April. The source is noted in parentheses after 
each report. 
  Chen Xitong Attends Donation Ceremony -- "The Jiahua Far 
East 
Company, Ltd. of Hong Kong recently donated 2 million yuan to 
Beijing municipality. The donated money was shared by Beijing's 
Greening Committee and the development foundation of the Beijing 
People's Art Theater. Chen Xitong, secretary of the Beijing 
Municipal CPC Committee, and Beijing mayor Li Qiyan attended the 
donation ceremony." (Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 
0429 GMT 4 Apr 94) 
  Li Ruihuan, Li Tieying, Li Lanqing Work as Advisers to 
Contest -- The first national "Golden Fan Award" new comic 
dialogue contest will be held soon. Li Ruihuan, Li Tieying, and 
Li Lanqing will serve as advisers to the contest. (Beijing 
XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0823 GMT 4 Apr 94) 
  Chen Xitong Attends Signing Ceremony -- The Beijing 
Municipal 
People's Government and Aviation Industries of China recently 
signed an agreement on jointly running the Beijing Aeronautics 
and Astronautics University which was run solely by Aviation 
Industries of China before. Chen Xitong, Li Qiyan, and Zhu Yuli 
attended the signing ceremony. (Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service 
in Chinese 0448 GMT 4 Apr 94) 
  Qian Qichen, Chen Xitong, Peng Peiyun on World Women's 
Congress -- Xu Zhijian, deputy secretary general of the State 
Council and vice chairman of the Chinese Organizing Committee 
for the Fourth World Women's Congress, told reporters: "The 
Party Central Committee and the State Council attach great 
importance to the preparatory work of the Fourth World Women's 
Congress and constantly inquire about it and give instructions. 
On 29 January, Hu Jintao, Chen Xitong, Qian Qichen, Chen Muhua, 
Peng Peiyun, and other leading comrades heard a briefing again 
on the work of the Chinese Organizing Committee." Hu Jintao, 
member of the Standing Committee of the CPC Central Committee 
Political Bureau and member of the Central Secretariat, said 
after hearing the briefing: "China's hosting of the World 
Women's Congress shows that this country is becoming more and 
more influential in the world and enjoying higher and higher 
international prestige. We have had more and more friends in 
the world. We should be determined to work with one heart and 
one mind to make the women's congress a success." Vice Premier 
and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said: "We should, through the 
World Women's Congress, establish China's image of reform, 
opening up, and social prosperity in the international 
community." Chen Xitong, secretary of the Beijing Municipal CPC 
Committee, said: "Beijing is determined to do a good job in 
preparatory work to ensure a smooth convocation of the world 
women's congress. We must make the congress a success and take 
advantage of it to show off Beijing's new appearance as a 
cosmopolis." (Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0158 
GMT 4 Apr 94) 
  Wu Bangguo Greets Establishment of Award Fund -- The 
Shanghai 
Petrochemical Spiritual Civilization Building Award Fund was set 
up on 26 March. Chen Zhili, deputy secretary of the Shanghai 
municipal party committee, addressed the inauguration ceremony 
and conveyed to the meeting the greetings and thanks extended by 
Wu Bangguo, member of the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau 
and secretary of the Shanghai Municipal CPC Committee, to 
Shanghai Petroleum Company Ltd. and Shanghai Jinshan Industrial 
Company for their donation of 5 million yuan, and establishment 
of the fund. (Shanghai JIEFANG RIBAO in Chinese 27 Mar 94 P 1) 
  Jiang Zemin Praises Shanghai Concert -- During two months of 
performance, the 1994 Shanghai Folk Music Festival yielded good 
social effects. General Secretary Jiang Zemin recently said in 
praise of the concert: "When Comrade Li Guifen was playing erhu 
[a two-stringed musical instrument], she was accompanied by 200 
children playing pipa [a plucked string musical instrument]. It 
was very touching. In this way, children's interest in music 
has been aroused." (Beijing Central Television Program One 
Network in Mandarin 1100 GMT 25 Mar 94) 
  Jiang Zemin, Others Mourn Deceased Comrade -- Zhang 
Zhenhuan, 
former chairman of the Science and Technology Committee of the 
Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for National 
Defense, died of illness on 23 March in Beijing at the age of 
79. At the funeral there were wreaths from Jiang Zemin, Rong 
Yiren, and Song Jian. Liu Huaqing, Zou Jiahua, and Zhang Zhen 
paid their last respects to Zhang Zhenhuan's remains at the 
Babaoshan Cemetery for Revolutionaries in the morning of 2 
April. (Beijing Central Television Program One Network in 
Mandarin 1100 GMT 2 Apr 94) 
  Li Peng Writes Inscription for Canal Renovation Project -- 
The renovation of the Hongqi Canal in Henan Province was 
completed on 2 April. Premier Li Peng wrote an inscription for 
the renovation project -- "The profound friendship existing 
between the armymen and the people is as long as the stream in 
the Hongqi Canal." (Beijing Central Television Program One 
Network in Mandarin 1100 GMT 3 Apr 94) 
  Liu Huaqing, Zhang Zhen Call on Veterans of No. 1 Field 
Army -- Liu Huaqing, member of the CPC Central Committee 
Political Bureau Standing Committee and vice chairman of the 
Central Military Commission; and Zhang Zhen, vice chairman of 
the Central Military Commission, went to the Jingxi Guesthouse 
on the morning of 5 April to visit veteran comrades of the 
editorial committee for the compilation of the battle history of 
the No. 1 Field Army. Liu Huaqing and Zhang Zhen joined the 
veteran comrades in recalling the glorious battles of the 
People's Liberation Army [PLA] during the liberation war. They 
said writing the PLA's battle history to recreate the 
magnificent scenes of the liberation war has great significance 
for preserving the Red Army's true qualities, for preserving the 
PLA's honorable traditions and "five revolutionary spirits," and 
for promoting socialist spiritual civilization. (Beijing XINHUA 
Domestic Service in Chinese 0952 GMT 5 Apr 94) 
  Li Peng, Others Write Inscriptions on Anniversary of Ancient 
Irrigation Project -- Sichuan's Dujiangyan, the world's oldest 
irrigation project, today marked its 2,250th birthday. Premier 
Li Peng wrote an inscription to mark the occasion. The 
inscription reads: "Sichuan has benefited from the great project 
of thousands of years." Tian Jiyun, vice chairman of the 
National People's Congress [NPC] Standing Committee; Yang Rudai 
and Qian Zhengying, both vice chairmen of the National Committee 
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference 
[CPPCC]; and state councilor Chen Junsheng also wrote 
inscriptions to mark the occasion. (Beijing XINHUA Domestic 
Service in Chinese 1335 GMT 5 Apr 94) 
  Jiang Zemin, Qiao Shi Write Inscriptions for Memorial Hall 
-- 
A ceremony was held in Henan's Linzhou city on 5 April to mark 
the completion of the memorial hall dedicated to martyr Sun 
Zhanyuan, a great international communist fighter, a first-class 
combat hero of the Chinese People's Volunteers Army, and a hero 
of the DPRK. Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC Central 
Committee, president of China, and chairman of the Central 
Military Commission, wrote an inscription for the hall. His 
inscription reads: "Martyr Sun Zhanyuan is immortal." An 
inscription written by Qiao Shi, member of the CPC Central 
Committee Standing Committee and chairman of the National 
People's Congress [NPC] Standing Committee, reads: "The heroic 
and noble spirit runs through the universe; the martyr spirit 
will carry on for thousands of years." Also writing 
inscriptions to mark the occasion were Qin Jiwei, vice chairman 
of the NPC Standing Committee, who was formerly commander of the 
15th Army of the Chinese Volunteers Army to which martyr Sun 
Zhanyuan belonged; and Li Desheng, member of the former Central 
Advisory Commission Standing Committee. (Beijing XINHUA 
Domestic Service in Chinese 1403 GMT 5 Apr 94) 
  Li Peng, Zou Jiahua, Li Lanqing Write Inscriptions for 
Entrepreneurs Activities -- China's first national entrepreneurs 
activities day was held in Fuzhou recently. Premier Li Peng and 
vice premiers Zou Jiahua and Li Lanqing wrote inscriptions to 
encourage entrepreneurs to be bold in seeking new ways to build 
a modern enterprise system, and to better display their 
pioneering spirit in the country's reform and opening up. 
(Beijing Central People's Radio Network in Mandarin 1030 GMT 5 
Apr 94) 
  Wu Bangguo, Others Lay Wreaths at Mausoleums -- To mark the 
45th anniversary of the liberation of Shanghai, party, 
government, and military leaders of Shanghai, and 
representatives from all sectors of the city went to the 
Shanghai Municipal Martyrs Mausoleum, the Soong Ching-ling 
Mausoleum, the Gaoqiao Martyrs Mausoleum, and the Baoshan 
Martyrs Mausoleum to sweep tombs, on the morning of 5 April. At 
0900, on behalf of the Shanghai Municipal CPC Committee, the 
municipal people's congress, the municipal government, and the 
municipal committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference [CPPCC], Wu Bangguo, member of the CPC 
Central Committee Political Bureau and secretary of the Shanghai 
Municipal CPC Committee; and Ye Gongqi, chairman of the Shanghai 
Municipal People's Congress Standing Committee, laid wreaths at 
the Shanghai Municipal Martyrs Mausoleum. Later, Wu Bangguo and 
other comrades laid wreaths at the Soong Ching-ling Mausoleum. 
(Shanghai People's Radio Network in Mandarin 2300 GMT 5 Apr 94) 
  Li Peng Writes Inscription for Agricultural Report -- 
According to a report from the fourth issue of the ZIGUANGGE 
magazine, the Ministry of Agriculture has organized 323 people 
to separately go to 100 counties in 25 provinces and autonomous 
regions to study agricultural problems. Premier Li Peng wrote 
an inscription for the Agriculture Ministry's 1993 report on the 
study of agricultural problems. The inscription reads: Go deep 
to grass-roots units to serve peasants; make scientific 
decisions to develop rural economy. (Beijing Central Television 
Program One Network in Mandarin 1100 GMT 6 Apr 94) 
  Li Tieying Urges Learning From Light Industrial Company -- 
At 
a meeting on 6 April to exchange the Beijing No. 1 Light 
Industrial Company's experience in taking comprehensive and 
interrelated measures to reform the enterprise, Li Tieying, 
state councilor and minister in charge of the State Economic 
Restructuring Commission, said: Beijing No. 1 Light Industrial 
Company not only has enlivened itself, but also has enlivened 
the country's light industry. Only by taking comprehensive and 
interrelated reform measures can we enable state-owned 
enterprises to free themselves from the current predicament. He 
stressed: In learning from the Beijing No. 1 Light Industrial 
Company, we should take local reality into consideration, focus 
on important issues, and strive to achieve practical results. We 
should particularly pay attention to properly handling state 
assets, and to preventing the loss of state assets. We should 
strive to preserve and increase the value of state assets by 
readjusting the makeup of resources and other essentials, and by 
transforming enterprise operating mechanisms. (Beijing Central 
Television Program One Network in Mandarin 1100 GMT 6 Apr 94) 

</TEXT>

