<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Satellite Launch Undergoes `Accidental Event' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Satellite Launch Undergoes `Accidental Event' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Text' of Circular </H4>

<F P=102> OW0804053094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0358 
GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0804053094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 8 Apr (XINHUA) -- A concerned department 
of the State Council today issued a circular on readjusting the 
plan for launching the first "Fengyun 2" satellite. The text of 
the circular is as follows: 
  China originally planned to use its Long-March 3 carrier 
rocket to launch the first "Fengyun 2" stationary meteorological 
satellite at the Xichang Satellite Launching Center in the near 
future. But, because an accidental event took place in the 
process of testing the satellite in the technical zone, damaging 
the satellite and workshops, the launching plan has been 
readjusted. China will make great efforts to complete the 
follow-up work to ensure the completion of other satellite 
launching plans for this year. 

</TEXT>

