<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Urges Study of Science, Technology </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiang Zemin Urges Study of Science, Technology </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704113894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1117 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 7 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President 
Jiang Zem in today urged Chinese officials at all levels to 
better arm themselves with knowledge of modern science and 
technology. 
  The president's call was contained in the foreword to a 
textbook entitled "ABC of Modern Science and Technology", which 
was published here today. 
  The book, produced by the State Science and Technology 
Commission upon the instruction of President Jiang, is intended 
for government officials at county level and above. 
  Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Central 
Committee 
of the Communist Party of China, said in the foreword that the 
period between now and the middle of the next century is vital 
for the prosperity of the Chinese nation. 
  He said that the current world situation characterized by 
peace and stability and the development of new science and 
technology have provided a precious opportunity for China to 
advance its economic development. 
  Jiang called on the whole nation to grasp the historical 
opportunity to keep track of the development of world science 
and technology and strive to transform the traditional 
industries and develop new ones. 
  He said that China must give full scope to science and 
technology in promoting economic growth so as to ensure a 
sustainable, fast and healthy development. 
  He urged officials at all levels to renew their knowledge in 
science and technology and keep abreast with modern development. 
  "Only by unswervingly keeping on learning and continuously 
renewing, can we improve our abilities of making policy 
decisions and the art of leadership," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

