<H3> <TI>   Fujian CPC Secretary Addresses Government Forum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujian CPC Secretary Addresses Government Forum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0804082794 Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0804082794 </F>
<F P=104>  Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The provincial government held a forum yesterday 
afternoon at the headquarters of the Fujian provincial Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference Committee, in which 
non-CPC representatives from all walks of life participated by 
invitation to air their opinions on the government work report. 
  Provincial CPC Secretary and Governor Jia Qinglin and 
leaders 
You Dexin, Wang Jianshuang, Liu Yongye, Zhang Jiakun, and Cao 
Jiufu attended the forum. Also present, were people in charge 
of the Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang, the 
China Democratic League, the Chinese Peasants' and Workers' 
Democratic Party, the China Democratic National Construction 
Association, the China Zhi Gong Dang, the Taiwan Democratic 
Self-Government League, the China Association for Promoting 
Democracy, the Jiusan Society, the All-China Federation of 
Industry and Commerce, and other public organizations concerned. 
  During the forum, participants fully expressed their 
opinions 
on the various ideas for the development of the province in all 
aspects presented by the government work report. They 
particularly contributed many very valuable opinions and 
suggestions on such issues as lightening the burden on the 
peasants, deepening the rural reform, transforming the 
operational mechanism of state-run enterprises, increasing 
investment in education and in scientific farming projects, 
establishing an effective supervision mechanism, and curbing 
corruption. 
  Provincial party committee Secretary and Governor Jia 
Qinglin 
addressed the forum, after hearing the opinions of non-CPC 
representatives from all walks of life, endorsing the opinions 
and suggestions presented by the forum participants and stating 
that their ideas would serve as a very useful reference for the 
government in policy making. 
  Comrade Jia Qinglin briefed the participants on the economic 
development and progress in reform in the province this year. 
He pointed out that this year will be a crucial one for the 
province in achieving sustained, rapid, and healthy development. 
The province's task this year is to carry on the reform, keep 
up development, and ensure stability, while maintaining a 
balance between these three aspects. 
  Jia Qinglin said: This province has initiated five reforms 
this year, specifically: Reform of the financial and taxation 
systems; the operation to introduce uniform foreign exchange 
rates; reform of the fundraising and financing systems; foreign 
trade reform; and reform of the banking system. As shown by the 
development over the past two months, smooth progress has been 
made in these reforms but more meticulous work must be done in 
the future. 
  Jia hoped that everybody will make concerted efforts and 
that 
all the democratic parties will play an active part in political 
involvement and work together to do a good job in building 
Fujian Province. 

</TEXT>

