<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongqing Reports Rapid Telecom Development </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongqing Reports Rapid Telecom Development </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704023394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0217 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704023394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chongqing, April 7 (XINHUA) -- Chongqing, a major 
industrial city in southwest Sichuan Province, has reported 
rapid expansion of its telecommunications network in recent 
years. 
  Officials from the telecommunications authority said the 
city's telephone lines had increased from 20,000 in 1988 to 
200,000 by the end of last year. 
  In 1993 alone, near 40,000 lines were installed at an 
investment of 510 million yuan. The figure equals the total 
number installed in the previous 40 years, according to the 
sources. 
  With the new opening of fiber optic lines to Wuhan and 
Chengdu and a satellite ground station, telecommunications 
between the city and the outside have become much easier, the 
sources said. 
  Nearly 95,000 direct call lines now connect the city with 
over 700 domestic cities and 185 countries across the world. 
  Meanwhile, the city's telecommunications network has become 
more diversified. It now handles more than 6,000 mobile phones 
and some 100,000 wireless pagers. 
  The sources said that, as the telephone network expands, 
applications for household telephones are piling up. 
  The sources disclosed that the city will invest a record one 
billion yuan this year to add another 210,000 lines to its 
telephone network. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

