<H3> <TI>   Li Presides Over Welcome </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Presides Over Welcome </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704214194 Beijing Central People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1030 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0704214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Hookup" program] </F>
  [Text] French Prime Minister Edouard Balladur arrived in 
Beijing this morning to begin a four-day official visit to 
China. Balladur is visiting China at the invitation of Premier 
Li Peng. During his visit, he will exchange views with Chinese 
leaders on further developing Sino-French relations, including 
economic and trade relations. 
  Among those who accompanied Prime Minister Balladur in his 
visit to China were his wife; the French foreign minister, the 
French minister of industry, post, telecommunications, and 
foreign trade; and the vice presidents of the French National 
Assembly. 
  This afternoon, Premier Li Peng presided over a welcoming 
ceremony for Prime Minister Balladur and his party on the square 
outside the eastern gate of the Great Hall of the People. Zhu 
Lin, Premier Li Peng's wife; Qian Qichen, State Council vice 
premier and concurrently foreign minister, and his wife, (Zhou 
Hanqiong); and Shi Dazhen, chairman of the Chinese Government 
Reception Committee and minister of power industry, attended the 
welcoming ceremony. 
  After the ceremony, the Chinese and French premiers held 
talks in the Great Hall of the People. 
  This afternoon, Wu Yi, foreign trade and economic 
cooperation 
minister, met with Gerard Longuet, French minister of industry, 
post, telecommunications, and foreign trade, who accompanied 
Balladur on his visit to China. 

</TEXT>

