<H3> <TI>   Qiao Shi Meets Berlin Delegation 7 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qiao Shi Meets Berlin Delegation 7 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704143394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1310 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704143394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 7 (XINHUA) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of 
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, met 
with a Berlin delegation led by the city's mayor Eberhardt 
Diepgen here this afternoon. 
  During the meeting Qiao congratulated Berlin and Beijing on 
cementing friendly-city ties. 
  Berlin left him with a deep and beautiful impression, Qiao 
said, when recalling his visit to Berlin in January. 
  Qiao noted that there will be more exchanges and cooperation 
between Beijing and Berlin, given sustained development of Sino- 
German relations of friendship. 
  He was glad that an agreement between Beijing and Berlin had 
been signed for their sister-city relations and a memorandum 
made on their exchanges from 1994 to 1995, Qiao said, hoping 
that exchanges will be strengthened and cooperation implemented 
in various fields. 
  Diepgen said that his current tour in Beijing has improved 
mutual understanding. 
  With the German-Chinese relations going on the right track, 
he said, new developments will be witnessed between Berlin and 
Beijing, and the two cities can cooperate for mutual benefit in 
infrastructure, telecommunications, environmental protection and 
revamping China's small- and medium-sized enterprises. 
  Li Qiyan, Beijing's mayor, attended the meeting. 

</TEXT>

