<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Interviews Portugal's Prime Minister Silva </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Interviews Portugal's Prime Minister Silva </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0804015894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0120 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0804015894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lisbon, April 7 (XINHUA) -- Portugal Prime Minister 
Anibal Cavaco Silva has said that his government hopes to 
further develop a comprehensive relationship with China. 
  In an interview with XINHUA reporters here on the eve of his 
trip to China, the prime minister said that the relations with 
China are one of Portugal's major foreign policy priorities. 
  He said his upcoming visit to China is aimed at promoting 
bilateral relations including economic cooperation and marking 
the 7th anniversary of the signing of the Sino-Portuguese joint 
declaration on Macao. 
  The prime minister said about 60 Portuguese entrepreneurs 
will accompany him on his tour to explore business opportunities 
in China. 
  On the issue of Macao, he said that the signing of the Joint 
Declaration was a historic event of great significance. 
  Portuguese government, Silva said, will continue to pursue 
three objectives on the issue: Stability, progress and 
confidence building. 
  He said that the Portuguese-Chinese Joint Liaison Group has 
been working well and the second half of Macao's transitional 
period will be smooth. 

</TEXT>

