<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-2288 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi068_h_94012" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-068 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  7 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Finland's Aho Visits Shanghai, Notes Economic Development </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finland's Aho Visits Shanghai, Notes Economic Development </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704122494 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1000 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Esko Aho, who is in Shanghai, has 
studied China's rapid economic development and new large 
projects. He was especially briefed on the Pudong special 
economic zone, which foreign enterprises are induced to invest 
in. Of Finnish enterprises, Nokia [telecommunications] is 
already represented there. The economic briefing by the 
Shanghai city leadership revealed that China will no longer 
establish any new special economic zones. 
  Prime Minister Aho also attended a ceremony in Shanghai at 
which Kone Oy [elevator and crane company] signed its latest 
elevator deal with China. The deal is worth nearly 30 million 
Finnish markkas. 

</TEXT>

