<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister To Leave for GATT Ministerial-Level Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister To Leave for GATT Ministerial-Level Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704121994 Taipei CNA in English 0739 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Y. C. Tsai] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, April 7 (CNA) -- Economic Affairs Minister 
P.K. Chiang, heading a 15-member delegation, will leave Saturday 
[9 April] for a ministerial-level meeting of the General 
Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT) scheduled to open in 
Marrakech, Morocco April 15. 
  As a GATT observer, Taiwan has been invited to attend the 
meeting, during which the 118 contracting parties will sign the 
agreement reached during the Uruguay Round talks in 
mid-December, Ministry of Economic Affairs officials said. 
  The GATT meeting will also make a final decision on the 
exact 
time for the establishment of the World Trade Organization 
(WTO), they pointed out. 
  Under the Uruguay Round accord, all GATT signatories are set 
to become members of the WTO, which will be given tougher 
enforcement powers to supersede GATT. 
  During the GATT meeting, the officials noted, Chiang will 
hold bilateral meetings with his counterparts from New Zealand, 
Canada, Australia, and the United States on problems involving 
Taiwan's accession to the Geneva-based world trade regulating 
body. 
  Taiwan, accepted as a GATT observer in September 1992, hopes 
to become a full member by the end of this year. 
  Meanwhile, the 17 Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) 
Forum ministers will hold an informal session during their stay 
in Morocco, the officials noted. 
  APEC groups Australia, Brunei, Canada, Mainland China, Hong 
Kong, Indonesia, Japan, Malaysia, Mexico, New Zealand, Papua New 
Guinea, the Philippines, Singapore, South Korea, Taiwan, 
Thailand, and the United States. 
  Chiang will proceed to Egypt for a three-day visit after the 
GATT meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

