<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Meets Mongolian Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng Meets Mongolian Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704142794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1309 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 7 (XINHUA) -- Premier Li Peng told 
visiting Mongolian Minister of External Relations Tserenpiliyn 
Gombosuren that he is looking forward to his upcoming official 
visit to the State of Mongolia in late April. 
  Gombosuren, who is here to make preparations for Li's visit, 
described Li's Mongolian tour as "an important event" in 
Mongolia- China relations and believed that the visit will be a 
success. 
  Li, expressing satisfaction at the smooth growth of Sino- 
Mongolian relations in the past few years, reaffirmed that the 
Chinese Government attaches importance to promoting 
good-neighborly Sino-Mongolian ties and hoped that the common 
border between China and Mongolia remains a border of peace and 
friendship. 
  Li described the changes that have taken place in Mongolia 
in 
recent years as resulting from the Mongolian people's choice and 
stressed that the Chinese Government respects such choice and 
hopes that Mongolia enjoys economic development and its people 
happiness. 
  Gombosuren assured Li that to consolidate and develop 
Mongolia- China ties is an important part of Mongolia's foreign 
policy. 
  He expressed admiration at the successes China has made in 
its reform and opening drive, saying that a stable and rapidly- 
developing China is very important to Mongolia. 

</TEXT>

