<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing Police Arrest Dissident Xu Wenli </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing Police Arrest Dissident Xu Wenli </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    3d Action in Week </H4>

<F P=102> HK0804084694 Hong Kong AFP in English 0826 GMT 8 April 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK0804084694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 8 (AFP)--Chinese dissident Xu Wenli 
was detained by police Friday, his wife said, in the third such 
action against pro-democracy activists in a week. 
  Xu was picked up by police on Thursday then returned home 
around midnight, but was detained again on Friday, the wife, 
Kang Tong, said. 
  Xu, 49, is a former activist in the 1978-79 pro-democracy 
movement who was freed last year after 12 years in jail. 
  In the past week, China's most famous dissident, Wei 
Jingsheng, and his secretary, Tong Yi, have also been detained. 

</TEXT>

