<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Satellite Launch Undergoes `Accidental Event' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Satellite Launch Undergoes `Accidental Event' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Plan `Readjusted' </H4>

<F P=102> OW0804043494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0427 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0804043494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 8 (XINHUA) -- China has readjusted 
the plan of launching its first "Fengyun 2" stationary 
meteorological satellite due to an accidental event. 
  The event took place while the satellite was tested in the 
technical zone, which damaged the satellite and the workshops on 
the testing site. 
  The satellite was originally planned to be launched by the 
"Long- March 3" carrier rocket in the Xichang Satellite 
Launching Center recently. 
  China is making great efforts to complete the follow-up work 
and ensure the full implementation of this year's launching plan. 

</TEXT>

